<div id="review_156502680" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/156502680" />
    <a title="William2" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4684009-william2"><img alt="William2" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530030828p2/4684009.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/156502680?book_show_action=true">Mar 24, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="William2" class="user" itemprop="url" name="William2" href="/user/show/4684009-william2">William2</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4684009-william2?shelf=japan">japan</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4684009-william2?shelf=20-ce">20-ce</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4684009-william2?shelf=translation">translation</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer156502680" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15469880835539898354">A worthwhile read even for a non-Christian like me who, nonetheless, has a deep and abiding intellectual interest in religion and spirituality. But VERY Christian. You have to have <i>some</i> empathy for that side of the story in order for it to be a satisfying read. If you&apos;re an atheist, not for you. No no no...</span>
  <span id="freeText15469880835539898354" style="display:none">A worthwhile read even for a non-Christian like me who, nonetheless, has a deep and abiding intellectual interest in religion and spirituality. But VERY Christian. You have to have <i>some</i> empathy for that side of the story in order for it to be a satisfying read. If you're an atheist, not for you. No no no...</span>
