<div id="review_1816129432" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1816129432" />
    <a title="Blake Crouch" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52535740-blake-crouch"><img alt="Blake Crouch" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1479398724p2/52535740.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1816129432?book_show_action=true">Nov 21, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Blake Crouch" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Blake Crouch" href="/user/show/52535740-blake-crouch">Blake Crouch</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1816129432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18198909636173161539">What a devastatingly brilliant novel about faith, fanaticism, love, suffering, and ultimately, the silence of God. Why does God allow pain to flourish in the world? Why does God stand silent while the world burns? This novel, about Jesuit Portuguese missionaries in Japan in the 17th Century is gorgeously rendered, asks the hardest of hard questions, and is simply one of the greatest novels I&apos;ve ever read. Very excited to see the upcoming film adaptation by Martin Scorsese. </span>
  <span id="freeText18198909636173161539" style="display:none">What a devastatingly brilliant novel about faith, fanaticism, love, suffering, and ultimately, the silence of God. Why does God allow pain to flourish in the world? Why does God stand silent while the world burns? This novel, about Jesuit Portuguese missionaries in Japan in the 17th Century is gorgeously rendered, asks the hardest of hard questions, and is simply one of the greatest novels I've ever read. Very excited to see the upcoming film adaptation by Martin Scorsese. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18198909636173161539" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


